            "advisory": "Affected versions of the PyJWT package are vulnerable to an Algorithm Allow-list Bypass due to improper handling of algorithm verification with `PyJWK` keys. The `jwt.decode()` and `jwt.decode_complete()` functions verify the `alg` field in the JWT header against a caller-supplied allow-list, but the actual signature verification is performed using the algorithm bound to the `PyJWK` object, not the one specified in the header. An attacker with control over a registered JWK/JWKS private key can exploit this vulnerability by signing a token with a disallowed algorithm, setting an allowed algorithm in the JWT header, and having the token accepted, thus bypassing verifier-side algorithm policies.",
