            "advisory": "Affected versions of the PyJWKClient package are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) due to unbounded JWKS endpoint requests. The `get_signing_key` method forces a new HTTP request to the JWKS endpoint for each JWT with an unknown `kid` value, bypassing the TTL cache and lacking rate limiting. An attacker can exploit this by sending numerous JWTs with arbitrary `kid` values, causing excessive outbound requests and potentially leading to reduced authentication availability.\nNote: The vulnerability surfaces only when a JWKS fetch fails; an attacker can attempt to provoke that with sustained unknown-kid traffic, but the outcome depends on upstream JWKS-endpoint behaviour (rate limiting, transient errors), which is beyond the attacker's control.",
